{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011YhcZchJQUuHB8Tae9T9eJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what was done and why:\n\n**Problem:** The replica set had 2 voting members (both data-bearing). With only 2 voters, majority requires 2/2 — losing either member makes a primary election impossible, so elections are unstable.\n\n**Fix:** Added `mongo-arb-0` (the already-running arbiter pod) to the replica set via `rs.addArb()`. The arbiter uses `emptyDir` (no persistent storage cost). The set is now PRIMARY + SECONDARY + ARBITER with **3 voting members, majority = 2** — it can survive losing one member.\n\n**Workaround required:** MongoDB 5.0+ blocks reconfig when adding an arbiter changes the implicit default write concern. Setting `defaultWriteConcern: { w: 1 }` explicitly unblocked the `addArb`.\n\n**Data:** The `app.test` collection still has 3 documents — unchanged."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":162,"cache_read_input_tokens":37998,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":162},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d71f105e-c09c-4f5a-a57f-d10b6f7e7f8f","uuid":"707b9502-19a1-4eee-b463-961a2edafa3f","request_id":"req_011CcRFihrUGmktZTVF9tVez"}
